  "informal_statement": "For all positive reals a, b, c: a/(b+c) + b/(a+c) + c/(a+b) >= 3/2 (Nesbitt's inequality).",
  "informal_proof_idea": "Clear denominators via div_add_div twice and le_div_iff₀, reducing to a polynomial inequality; close with nlinarith using the three pairwise-difference square hints plus positivity of the pairwise products. A bare nlinarith attempt on the raw division goal fails first (see the paired negative example negative.inequalities.nesbitt_bare_nlinarith_division_failure.v1): nlinarith cannot reason through division atoms without clearing denominators.",
  "formal_statement_pp": "theorem nesbitt_three_var (a b c : ℝ) (ha : a > 0) (hb : b > 0) (hc : c > 0) : a / (b + c) + b / (a + c) + c / (a + b) ≥ 3 / 2",
